* Iron Raptor waited calmly for the three bots before her to answer her question, eagerly wondering just what they had in mind for the Ark.
Could it to be to move it or something similar to that?
She knew that it would need heavy repair and that would take a bit of time, but with Iris, herself and some of her Maximals they would get the job done.
Suddenly her scanners alerted of her of an intruder in one of the quarters of the ship, further investigation telling her that it was being taken care of.
But then another sweep of the ship alerted her of another presence, one that she hadn't known about and seemed to be in an area that they didn't belong.
They were in the engine room, an unknown signature but one the read Maximal.
It must be a new bot, one that she was sure didn't belong where it was.
Iron Raptor looked at Arcangle with a slight smile, she would take care of this little problem for a moment.*

" If you excuse me, gentlemen, I have to take care of a slight problem, I'll only be a moment."

* And with that she turned from them and walked towards the end of the room, a smaller room branched off from the Conference Room.
She entered and the door shut behind her, looking around quickly and discovering that it was a smaller conference room. One for smaller audiences.
She sighed and opened her com-link to the new bot 
( Feline ).*


" Being 315, this is Iron Raptor, Maximal Commander. It seems as if you're in a restricted area, please report to me in Conference Room 6-3. We'll see if we can get you straightened out.Thank You."

* With that she deactivated her com-link and exited the room, walking back up to the three bots. She expected the new bot to report to her as she was asked, while she dealt with this.
Iron Raptor looked at the three bots and sighed.*

" Thank you for waiting. Now, what is you needed to speak to me about?"
